column36:
🚨SB 22: Proponent Testimony Call to Action🚨

This Wednesday, Feb. 3rd, there is proponent (support) testimony for SB 22. 
(the new and improved version of SB 311.)

➡️What does SB 22 do? 

Legislative analysis summary:
  
• Permits the General Assembly to rescind orders and rules issued by the Governor or Ohio Department of Health (ODH).

• Establishes the Ohio Health Oversight and Advisory Committee, and grants the Committee the power to rescind certain orders and rules issued by the Governor and ODH.
*****(NOTE: Gov. orders are evaluated by the commitee 11 days after they are written. The commitee will consist of 6 members: 3 Senators [2-R, 1-D.] appointed by Senate President Huffman, and 3 representatives [2-R, 1-D] appointed by House Speaker Cupp.)******

• Limits the duration of a public health state of emergency to 30 days unless extended BY the General Assembly. 

• During a public health state of emergency, requires the Governor and ODH to REPORT to the President of the Senate and the Speaker of the House of Representatives ANY actions taken in response to the emergency.

• Subjects existing orders and rules issued by the Governor or ODH to review and rescission by the General Assembly and the Committee.
****(NOTE: Allows general assembly to vote on a simple resolution (at any time) that rescinds an order by the Governor. If passed, it can NOT be vetoed and the order no longer stands.)****

•The bill removes the word “ultimate” from existing law describing ODH’s authority over matters of quarantine and isolation.

• When there is an emergency determined regarding a tainted consumable product,
 then it changes the  wording from being described as a “public health emergency”, to instead specifying it as an “adulterated consumer product emergency”. 

——

column31: The results of a study by researchers at Stanford University, the University of Nebraska, and Evolve BioSystems suggest that the vast majority of infants in the United States may exhibit a substantial deficiency in an important gut bacterium that is key to breast milk utilization and immune system development, as well as protection against gut pathogens linked to common newborn conditions such as colic and diaper rash. “The infant gut is essentially a blank slate at birth, and rapidly acquires bacteria from mom and the environment. We were surprised not only by the extensive lack of good bacteria, but the incredibly high presence of potentially pathogenic bacteria and an environment of antibiotic resistance that appears to be so widespread. The infant gut microbiome in the United States is clearly dysfunctional, and we believe this is a critical factor underpinning many of the infant and childhood ailments we see today across the country.” said study co-author Karl Sylvester. Breastfeeding is far beyond just food. It is essential to an infant’s long term growth and development in many ways. It’s not “one of the ways to feed a baby,” it is the biologically optimal way to feed a baby.

column31: Allopathy believes strictly in germ theory. That is, they honestly think that whether or not a person gets sick is nearly solely dependent on whether or not they're exposed to an illness, and the amount of virus/bacteria that enters their body. Exposure to high viral/bacterial loads = illness. So, their goal is to intervene to stop that from happening, by asking people to wear masks, wash hands, and get v@xxynes. They will never stray from this advice, even when we reach the point of ridiculous (if we haven't already). It's what they know. And if you reject these things they're offering, you are rejecting THEM. You are rejecting what is most fundamental to them. In reality, while exposure to germs *can* make you sick, you also have an immune system. Your body is more or less susceptible to illness depending on how you take care of it. If you have the right balance of vitamins and minerals, low inflammation, good gut flora, your immune system can kick into gear rapidly and fight off anything you might be exposed to before you ever actually "get sick." ("Getting sick" is your immune system failing to mobilize fast enough to get rid of unfriendly germs and bring your body back into balance. It has to ramp up and use stronger defenses to get rid of those germs, which produces symptoms.) If you take care of your body, it doesn't mean you'll never get sick. It means you're much less likely to. It means if you do get sick, it's likely to be milder and of shorter duration. Will you keep taking advice from the mainstream, who have nothing but fear and ridiculous ideas to offer? Or will you learn to take care of your health the natural way, and live without so much fear? If we keep going down this path, we'll have people who are literally terrified of everyone and whose physical and mental health is not good. On the other hand, we'll have people who make healthy choices and take moderate risks, but are also responsible (staying home when sick, washing hands). Which side will you be on?
column34: Masks and v@xxynes do NOT support your immune system. Vitamins, minerals, exercise, water, nutrient-dense foods, fresh air and sleep support your immune system. Earthley -wellness

column31: Most women are subject to routine pelvic exams during pregnancy...early, late, and during labor. But did you know these are often NOT necessary? Early in pregnancy, cervical exams are used to "confirm" pregnancy. A simple, non-invasive urine test can do the same thing. Late in pregnancy, cervical exams are used to "predict" labor. While a pelvic exam *may* benefit a woman who is pre-term and having signs of impending labor (via the "Bishop score"), there is no benefit to women who are full-term and simply wondering how many more days it will be! During labor, there is also little benefit. Most providers use cervical exams for their own knowledge, so that they can try to predict when they'll be needed for delivery. It doesn't impact the progress of labor or improve the outcomes for mom or baby. Pelvic exams can also introduce foreign bacteria and increase the risk of infection to both mother and baby. Some women find the exams extremely uncomfortable mentally and physically, especially if they are performed frequently or by different providers. They also immediately shift the vaginal flora, which can impact the baby's gut development (but no studies have been done to see what the long-term impact might be). One situation in pregnancy where an exam may be advised is if a woman has had a previous second-trimester loss, or is having symptoms of very pre-term labor. Cervical shortening is highly predictive of early labor, and women can get progesterone supplements to help sustain the pregnancy until they are full-term. However, "repeated" exams do not improve outcomes with pre-term labor. (An ultrasound may also work to detect a shortening cervix.) If you don't want a pelvic exam, you have the right to say NO (until or unless you change your mind or something goes wrong). You can also learn how to check yourself for dilation during labor, if you want to know. Whether or not you have an exam, baby *will* be born. 🙂 Sources: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/20159393:=:https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/20159393/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5503468/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23857468:=:https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/23857468/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3560273/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/20556763:=:https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/20556763/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/10076131:=:https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/10076131/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/28475099:=:https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/28475099/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/21551402:=:https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/21551402/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3647734/

column31: #scienceisunsettling The Arsenic Green Dress - “In 1775, Swedish and German pharmaceutical chemist Carl Wilhelm Scheele created a new green pigment which he named Scheele’s Green. The brilliantly vivid green would soon be the allure of the Georgians and Victorians of the era. The dazzling green would be the front of fashion, and come to decorate homes and bodies alike, but to the unexpected detriment of all whom it touched. This green was made with arsenic. It’s amazing how in the 1800s Scheele’s Green would be on wallpapers and ballgowns, but by the 1930s it would be relegated as an insecticide. Together with some other arsenic greens: Emerald Green, Scheele’s Green, Paris Green, a deadly shade of green would soon be found in nearly everyone’s homes, and touching everyone’s skin. This vibrant shade of green would be used as color for paper, wallpapers and paper hangings, in paints, wax candles, on children’s toys, on artificial flowers (worn by women), and as a dye for cotton and linen, which would then become clothing. Because it dyed fabric bright green, arsenic also ended up in dresses, gloves, shoes, and artificial flower wreaths that women used to decorate their hair and clothes. At its height of popularity, seven tons of Scheele’s green was being shipped out of England in 1860. These arsenic greens were also used a food dye for sweets such as green blancmange. Bakers used arsenic green as food coloring, and some restaurants even added it to their drinks. In 1858, in the deadly Bradford sweets poisoning, twenty-one people perished from arsenic-laced hard candies sold by a local character known as Humbug Billy. The toxicity of dye made with emerald green was not initially recognized, until the recipe was published in 1822. But it did not make a huge difference. People were still willing to use these toxic dyes. In 1861, 19-year-old Matilda Scheurer had worked in a factory where she dyed fake flowers green, but died from her exposure. She convulsed, vomited, and foamed at the mouth. Her bile was green, and so were her fingernails and the whites of her eye. An autopsy found arsenic in her stomach, liver, and lungs. Full post: https://circleofmamas.com/health-news/the-arsenic-green-dress-when-fashion-was-deadly/

column31: There has been a lot of confusion about supplements lately. Some people have gotten the idea that "if a little is good, more must be better" when it comes to certain nutrients. Or, they've confused the amounts that are beneficial when not feeling well with amounts that should be used daily. Here's where we stand: for the most part, in most situations, mega-doses are bad. Every vitamin and mineral has an 'agonist' and an 'antagonist' in the body -- usually several. When someone takes a regular mega-dose of one nutrient, it causes the body to have high levels of that nutrient, PLUS all of the agonists. It causes deficiencies in all of the antagonists. For example, calcium and magnesium compete for absorption in the body. Take way too much calcium and it will lead to a magnesium deficiency. What we really need is balance. That's the holistic view. No nutrient is more important than another (generally speaking); we need all of them, in the right amounts, to be healthy. We trust nature, and our own instincts, for this balance. Healthy foods and herbs have what we need, in the right amounts. Mega-dose pills don't. (Ever notice that your pee turns bright yellow after taking a supplement? That's all the vitamins you didn't absorb.) Stick with nature. Naturally healthy and in balance.

column31: Just as @justtheinserts is being asked to debunk or shed light on @dr.risahoshino #vaers post, some people are hitting me up as well.... What I will say is: have you actually tried to submit a VAERS report? I tried and I quit after 5 minutes. It was for my boyfriends step grandpa, he had a pneumococcal shot and then a flu shot and then was hospitalized shortly after, like a few days. Had a high fever, was shaky and weak. Because I know, and you know, reactions like this, especially reactions that result in hospitalizations *should* be reported to #vaers So I, trying to be helpful, tried to submit it. But I didn’t know his address, his doctor, the vaccine names and lots. I didn’t know anything! I would need access to his medical records. I didn’t even know the name of the hospital he was at. I messaged his son, our uncle, and said: look it’s asking too many questions you have to submit. Did he report the reaction? I guarantee you 100% NO. It’s involved. And when your father is in the hospital it’s the last thing on your mind. It’s not an easy thing to do. So to suggest there are false reports, those would stick out like a sore thumb. And probably never even get published. It’s a laborious, involved process. If someone thinks it’s so easy to fake, I would love to see you try. I have talked to mothers whose babies died shortly after vaccines, and their doctors didn’t even submit the reports. It just doesn’t happen. Ask around. If you or your child had a vaccine reaction: did you submit a VAERS report? Why or why not? If yes, what was the experience like? Secondly, it’s completely dismissive to say that vaers is filled with false reports. It’s just another way to slander and abuse people who experienced a vaccine reaction. It’s shameful. It’s actually disgusting, especially coming from a healthcare professional. Here’s a study (not the Harvard pilgrim one) that found that only 17% of health care providers had EVER reported to vaers. 👉🏼https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/23597717/

column31: Time for another Earthley fact-check! The claim: wearing two or three masks is more effective than one mask. The rating: partly false. There's NO evidence to suggest that three masks is really right. And no guidance on the construction of said masks. It matters greatly how the mask fits, the materials it is made of, etc. And it's not necessary to wear these extra special masks since these new strains are not more deadly than the current strains. column31: "Government officials keep rolling their eyes and assigning rude slurs to people who won't just do what they say. Hey! If you want our cooperation, then you'd better change how you're treating us. Here's what we're looking for.... Show Us the Data Making proclamations based on assumptions, incomplete science, or numbers that aren't adding up isn't good enough. Show us the studies, how you're collecting the data, what exactly you used to come to your conclusions. Put all the info online so we can review it ourselves. Acknowledge Subtleties Things aren't black and white. Maybe some things are beneficial in some situations, or when done certain ways, but not others. Don't make blanket statements anymore. Tell us the WHOLE truth. We don't need the message broken down into soundbites. Apologize if You're Wrong Sometimes, you're going to make a bad decision based on faulty data, or let the stress get to you. You're human, we get that. But when it happens, take responsibility and apologize for it. Don't just pretend that your flip-flopping or harsh statements were justified or that they didn't happen. Hear Our Concerns You CANNOT make simple rules that apply across the board. People have different situations, needs, and concerns. Listen to them. Make space for them. Don't dismiss people with concerns as childish, ignorant, or difficult. Take them seriously. Be Respectful We're sure it's hard to be a leader right now, with everyone as divided as they are. But your job is to bring people together, not pit them against one another. Do not encourage people to report each other. Do not call your constituents names. Speak respectfully of everyone. Be the example. Ask Us, Don't Order Us We're not children. We're capable of understanding the situation, looking at all the facts, and coming to our own conclusions. We don't want to be ordered around. If there's something you think would be beneficial, then lay out the facts, and ask us respectfully. The people who can, probably will. Our issue with everything has never been that we think it's all just some conspiracy theory, or that we don't want to take care of other people, or that we're being contrary just to be contrary. We're not convinced by the science, we don't feel respected, and we're worried about what the future holds. Come to the table with us as equals, and we'll be more likely to hear what you have to say. Keep insulting us and acting like we're idiots, well...prepare to be opposed forever.

column31: Former vice president of Pfizer, Dr. Michael Yeadon raised concerns that COVID-19 vaccines may impair fertility, and has petitioned the European regulator along with Dr. Wodarg for an immediate halt of the vaccines. Dr. Yeadon and Dr. Wodarg state that the mRNA shot codes for spike proteins which are syncitin homologous proteins and that there is potential for the immune system to develop a response against syncytin-1 which is a protein that is fundamental for the formation of a placenta. He states if this happens a woman could become “infertile indefinitely”. Yeadon says the trials have not addressed this concern at all and so while there is no evidence this would happen he says there is equally no evidence that it wouldn’t, and the onus is on the manufacturer to rule this out before vaccinating millions of women worldwide. They have literally no data on this. Many articles have attempted to “debunk” this claim, however they use “strawman arguments.” For instance it takes an article which misquotes Yeadon in the headline arguing against things he never said. It then brings in a microbiologist to patronizingly explain that the shot doesn’t inject viral proteins but rather mRNA …but nobody is claiming otherwise. it mentions the term conspiracy theorist in the second paragraph. It’s all designed to smear Yeadon as a lunatic, whereas he was head of research and development for Pfizer for many years so there can be few people in the world better qualified to speak about this topic. He himself stated that there’s no evidence it would cause infertility, but equally there is no evidence it wouldn’t. Yet the article falsely targets him for claiming that it would. The vaccinations are expected to raise antibodies against the spike proteins of SARS-CoV-2. However, spike proteins also contain syncytin-homologous proteins, which are essential for the formation of the placenta in mammals such as humans. It must be absolutely excluded that a vaccine against SARS-CoV-2 triggers an immune reaction against syncytin-1, as otherwise infertility of indefinite duration in vaccinated women could result. https://circleofmamas.com/health-news/covid-19-vaccine-and-infertility/ #fertility #infertility

column31: A lot of people believe that the oldest drugs, the ones that have been on the market the longest, are the safest. After all, we have decades of data/use to prove it.... Nope. Up until the 1980s, drugs underwent basically one test: does it kill people (at reasonable doses)? If not, it was approved. No further evidence was needed. After disasters like thalidomide, researchers finally realized that a greater body of evidence was needed to determine how safe a drug actually was. Many of the drugs that remain on the market today are simply "assumed" to be safe because of their long history of use. There are very few, if any, studies about their overall effects on the body. In some cases, researchers don't actually understand their mode of action. It's likely that some -- if not many -- of these drugs, if they were up for new approval today, with greater studies required, would never receive approval at all.

column36:
Although Hepatitis B vaccine is for a sexually transmitted disease primarily spread from injection drug use and among homosexual men with multiple partners, or those with multiple sexual partners, since 1991 it has been given to newborns on the first day of birth regardless of whether the child is at risk through maternal exposure, and it has been mandated for school children in many states between 1994 and 1998. 

So the question is: Why??

From this research paper: 

 “The enactment of the Vaccines for Children program coincided with a broadened set of hepatitis B vaccine recommendations by the ACIP, which now urged that all 11- and 12-year-olds be vaccinated against the virus. The committee stressed that universal infant vaccination should continue, but that adolescent vaccination was needed to cause disease incidence to decline more quickly. Health officials were blunt in justifying the widespread vaccination of youth. Vaccinating high-risk adults had proved enormously difficult, an ACIP statement noted, but routine childhood vaccination would obviate vaccination of adults.“We do not feel that targeting adults for vaccination has worked,” a CDC official told the Boston Globe. “This will be the first time,” she went on, “that a vaccine is recommended for children to prevent a disease that primarily occurs in adults.”

So those adults who were actually at risk for the disease didn’t care enough to vaccinate themselves, so every newborn and school age child needs to bear the risk of a medical intervention meant for a small group of adults making specific  lifestyle choices?

Do public health policy makers truly have the best interest of children at heart?

Vaccines typically work by causing DAMP (by killing cells in our body with adjuvants). On the other hand, our immune system also can detect conserved or previously memorized patterns (PAMP) that it inherently knows is bad. mRNA detected outside the cell is considered bad because it indicates one of two things: a cell died, or that it’s a virus.So mRNA, the very instruction set that needs to get inside our immune cells (those are the target cells that the vaccine is trying to infect with mRNA), is also an immunostimulatory factor. 2. Polyethyline Glycol (PEG) infused in Lipid Nanoparticles Because mRNA is so unstable (which is why Pfizer’s vaccine requires extreme cold storage to remain stable), one way to make it more stable is to envelope the mRNA in a lipid layer. If you are familiar with lyphospheric vitamin C, this is a very similar concept, to envelope vitamin C in a lipid sphere in order to increase cellular uptake and bioavailability. The same holds true for mRNA. The lipid layer in some mRNA vaccines (I’m not certain of which ones), can be infused with polyethyline glycol, which would act as the adjuvant.I know PEG has gotten a bad rap, but it also serves other purposes, like preventing the lipid envelope from binding to other proteins in our bodies, and to allow the mRNA to escape the envelope after it bypasses the cellular wall. Our bodies tend to form anti-PEG antibodies when exposed to it. The lipid layer can also contain other pro-inflammatory factors that would stimulate a Th1 response. 3. The lipid envelope contains or the mRNA encodes for proinflammatory precursors Since the lipid envelope contains the mRNA payload, the envelope may contain other proinflammatory factors in order to start an immune response. column31: Shared via @lovepeaceandvalor “I’ll forever be grateful for the moment I decided to take my own and my kids’ health into my hands When I became a first-time mom, I had a gut feeling that vaccines were no good and that there was no way that injecting questionable ingredients into the human body could be good for anybody. Despite my mama instincts, I decided that I hadn’t done enough research to not vaccinate and to trust the professionals After my firstborn stopped sleeping through the night following her shots, my original intuition about vaccines only grew and I stopped taking her in to her ‘well’ visits to avoid pressure on continuing vaccines. She ended up being my most alert and advanced child and started walking on her own without help by 7 months My second baby wasn’t so lucky. We were well-established with a pediatrician and again, despite my gut feeling, I trusted my doctor and took her to every ‘well’ visit up until she was 24 months old. In comparison to her sister health-wise, I noticed she would catch more colds far more than her older sister would When I had my third and last baby, I was even more iffy about vaccines but being as I worked as a Medical Assistant at the pediatric office she was a patient at, I was afraid of being mocked and belittled by the doctor and that they would kick us out of the practice Then, at her 6 month ‘well’ visit, after receiving her CDC-scheduled shots, she experienced an extreme adverse reaction and developed seizures. I was terrified. I had the strongest nagging voice in my head that I needed to do more research on vaccines, so I did. I never took her back, or any of my children for that matter and they have all remained vaccine-free since When we were vaccinating, my kids were almost always sick with the exception of my oldest who received the least amount of vaccines in her life. Now, my kids are the healthiest they’ve been and don’t get sick anymore The only vaccine we need (and already have) is our immune systems, love, fresh air, water, vitamins and foods that contain the “medicine” I will never agree or condone mandated vaccines. Whether you are for or against vaccines, I think we all can agree..

column31: D E T O X. This month's hottest buzz word. But, what about drainage? It’s a VERY important word that doesn’t get nearly the amount of attention it should. I've posted about drainage and detox and their differences before, here is a review. Drainage and detox are not the same thing, even though they are often interchanged ideas. Drainage is a multi-organ dependent process of allowing the release of substances such as waste and toxins, phase 1. While detox is the actual process of removing them, phase 2. Before you jump into a detox, new supplement routine, or pathogen killing protocol, do yourself a favor and FIRST find out if your drainage pathways are clear and open. Your body will thank you for it. A lot of toxin reabsorption happens when we don't drain properly, leading to an unnecessary Herxheimer Reaction/healing crisis, as well as lowered immunity, hormone imbalance, fatigue, aches/pains, dental issues, digestive concerns, emotional/mood ups and downs to name a few. Furthermore, you are more susceptible to all the concerns that come from having a heavy toxin load. Here are the drainage pathways/channels of elimination ... +The Glymphatic System (the brain “lymph”) +The Lymphatic System +The Liver (and gb) +The Lungs +The Kidneys +The Skin +The Blood +The Colon This is a very critical operating system for your body. If you have blockage, flow issues and stagnancy in one system, we see a cascading effect in others. When we sleep, we brain drain in the most literal sense, our brain squeezes and releases, moving glymphatic fluid around cerebral centers where it picks up amyloid protein, pathogens and quells inflammation. This glymphatic fluid drains downward into the lymphatic system through lymph vessels in the head and neck. Along with its associated vessels and nodes , lymph fluid circulates critical immune cells and toxins, to be delivered to the liver. The liver is our number 1 detoxification organ! It pushes over 70% of toxins into our bile which it stores in the gallbladder. Because bile production is very costly, requiring lots of energy, bile is often reabsorbed, as well as the bi-products it contains. The liver additionally drains into the colon and kidney. The kidney process waste through their nephrons and maintain hydration of the colon. The lymphatic system collects excess fluid that drains from cells and tissue throughout the body and returns it to the bloodstream, which is then recirculated through the body. The colon is the final removal site for this extensive process of waste removal. . . . How can you find out if you’re ready for a detox? Here is a checklist of questions to ask yourself. If you answered “no” to any of these questions, a detox COULD DO YOU MORE HARM THAN GOOD. Why? Because your drainage pathways need to be attended to - opened and clear. Implementing this information has been life changing for myself personally and for all of my clients. I’m so excited to share this information with you to support you on your healing journey! I promise you, IT WILL CHANGE YOUR LIFE! I'll be posting the drainage funnel with details soon, stay tuned! 🌪 Our drainage pathways have an order in which they move waste out of the body - just like a funnel. If one of the pathways is blocked, every pathway above it will not be able to drain properly → This is why we look at drainage from the BOTTOM-UP. Start with the colon. column31: **Long Post** Over the last year, a LOT of people have become more concerned with medical freedom and especially with v@c with what's going on in the world. They have questions; they're not getting satisfactory answers. The mainstream has bungled the way they've handled this and confidence in the v@x program is getting lower. They wrote studies about this mid-2020. They knew if the c-v@x roll out didn't go well that confidence in the entire program would drop. Expect to see a lot of stories about AV people turning PV over the next year. They will be using these as propaganda to make the AV crowd look a certain way, to try to do damage control. These stories will all feature specific things: 1. The person will be AV very suddenly and out of nowhere 2. The person will turn to AV because of online groups of documentaries that scare them into it (but they don't do any research, of the "research" they do is heavily biased and incorrect, only they're too ignorant to realize it yet) 3. The AV crowd is a cult that forces people to be carbon copies -- to never say you might V or trust any mainstream anything 4. They had an illness or contact with a rational PV person and there was some "ah-ha" moment 5. They started actually doing research and realized it only supports the PV side 6. They started "trusting science" again and listening to doctors 7. They were bullied and attacked mercilessly by the AV crowd for speaking up for science 8. They're grateful to modern medicine and to be out of that uneducated cult 9. Be nice to the AV crowd, because they're hapless fools; they don't mean to be so ignorant, they just don't know and need patience and facts to make them see the error of their ways These people will join the AV crowd out of nowhere. They will immediately join all of the groups and try to friend request dozens or hundreds of people in the span of a few weeks. They will want a lot of attention. They will continue to debate with both sides, "to be fair." They will be unable or unwilling to answer any tough questions about what research they did or why they're AV. And if anyone calls them out, they will gaslight the heck out of them, claiming bullying and hate because they didn't toe the right line. And then they will walk away from AV, share their story of catching themselves and their kids up, and then the national media will pick up the stories. They may be plants/controlled opposition. They may be confused people who don't understand the issue and are used by the PV crowd. We've seen this several times now. And I think we will see it several more. To combat this, here is what you can do: 1. If someone comes out of nowhere and starts friending everyone and joining all the groups, hang back. Don't let this person get into a position of leadership or influence. Tell them to sit back and read and listen and learn, not try to get themselves front and center. (If they throw a fit about this, they're likely CO.) 2. If someone seems to be wishy-washy, uneducated, or starting drama, ignore them. Don't give them attention. Group admins can point them towards studies and close threads. Don't let them be a distraction. 3. If they insist on being a spokesperson or making a public spectacle, distance from them. Leaders should make it clear that this person is acting independently and not as a leader/spokesperson in our movement. (Only those with years of proven work should ever be a leader. Never newbies.) 4. Insist on educating yourself and educating others with studies and facts. If the majority of us are speaking from a place of knowledge, the few people that are speaking from emotion will be drowned out. 5. Consistently share your stories and your knowledge so that people understand what the AV crowd is *really* like. We don't have to convince PV people, only those who don't yet know. 6. Be kind and polite as much as possible. Never ridicule, send threats, or get nasty with someone. If you're angry, go vent to a friend (and walk away from the CO). These CO people aren't worth your energy, and when you are rude to them it only solidifies their views and gives them ammunition to use against use later. It's important we try not to let this happen right now, when the mainstream is looking for cracks to exploit. They can't win any other way, so that's what they're going to do. We are stronger, and we are smarter. People who aren't really part of the community shouldn't be speaking for the community, and that anyone who is on the fence shouldn't listen to these sensationalized stories. This is a really long post, but thanks for reading if you got all the way down here.

column31: "I had to post this moment I captured this afternoon, hope you enjoy. I stopped by Dollar Tree off Lakeland this afternoon to pick up wrapping paper, and I couldnt help but be drawn to this. This older gentleman very softly said to the lady in the photo, "Mam, would you mind helping me out with something?" As she nodded, "yes, of course, what do you need?" "I need help picking out a birthday card." "Who is it for?", she asked. This is where I started to sniffle. "It's for me, if I wake up tomorrow, I'll be 85." "My wife wanted to get me something, but she's very sick and cannot leave the house, and I want her to know I got a birthday card from her." He continued on to tell stories of how they've been married since they were teenagers, had children, and how she was there for him while he served in military. It was the picture of love you only read about. I felt so privileged to get to hear this conversation. Melted my heart. Hope you all enjoy." Credit: Louisa Lenore McKinney

column31: Check the media, and there are always dark, vague warnings about the "dangers" of alternative medicine. We decided to dive in and see what evidence there actually was.... Some studies show as many as 70% of Americans are using at least one prescription drug at any given time. Many of them end up hospitalized due to adverse reactions, and several die. The estimations here are based on people using drugs each year vs. the known number of adverse reactions and deaths. Now, the mainstream likes to make several arguments about the true "dangers" of alternative medicine, all of which read like conspiracy theories (because they are). First they start out with, not that many people use it, so the risks to those who do are probably greater -- but that's not true. About a third of all people in the US use at least one herbal remedy each year. Then they mutter about how supplements are "unregulated" and "untracked" and we have no idea how many people MIGHT be having adverse reactions. But they can't pull out more than a small handful of cases studies -- typically 8 - 10 per year. (Fewer than 1 in a million!) There's not exactly a huge upswell of users complaining about how terrible herbs are and demanding they be pulled off the market...unlike some pharmaceutical products we can think of. It's true that the majority of adverse reactions that have been documented from supplements occurred either as allergic reactions, improper use, improperly made supplements, or were never proven to be tied to the supplement at all (just "associated with"). Almost never do properly-made, properly-used supplements cause adverse effects, outside of allergies. Finally, they get upset because herbal supplements are "preventing people from using real medicine" (by which they mean allopathy). First of all, looking at these numbers, that seems like it's a GOOD thing in some cases.... It also doesn't take into consideration the number of people who are choosing herbal remedies because allopathy already failed to work for them. Why does the mainstream give allopathy and all its damages a free pass, while darkly condemning herbal remedies without any evidence to do so? Their dire, anti-science rantings sound like the "tin foil hat" nonsense they accuse *us* of! Smart people are capable of cutting through the lies and looking at the data for themselves. And smart people will clearly see the truth here, and choose the safest option whenever possible -- natural

column31: Adjuvants are what makes vaccines work inside the body, or signal the immune system. Typically adjuvants are the little bomb that explodes and alerts your body that a pathogenic invader has entered. It’s necessary when using a dead or inactivated bacteria or virus, which isn’t capable of infecting our cells. Moderna’s vaccine doesn’t contain a killed microbe, and doesn’t contain aluminum, so the big question is: what is making the vaccine signal the immune system? A friend of mine spoke to someone on the inside, and asked him what the “immunostimulatory” signal was… because since their vaccine does not contain any “adjuvants” per say, what causes the immune system to respond? Obviously the spike protein is not going to initiate the response. So apparently, if you read the patents for Moderna (like the one here), the mRNA that Moderna encodes for is not just the spike protein. The Moderna mRNA encodes for two things: the COVID spike protein AND bacterial flagellin. If you recall, aluminum adjuvants cause DAMP (Damage Associated Molecular Patterns) by causing damage to cells. The other immunostimulatory signal that can instantiate an immune response is PAMP (Pathogen Associated Molecular Pattern). PAMPs are conserved patterns that the immune system inherently knows is dangerous. So, at least with Moderna’s vaccine, you know that cells are not just producing COVID spike proteins, but they’re also producing PAMPs as well, in the form of bacterial flagellin. which is a potent PAMP. I don’t have any information on Pfizer’s mRNA, so I’m not entirely sure what the immunostimulatory signal is… but hopefully that will give you some food for thought. Full post/ shareable post: https://circleofmamas.com/health-news/modernas-secret-adjuvant/ #moderna #adjuvant #covid19 #covidvaccine #immunereaction #immuneresponse #covidvacccine #igottheshot #igotmyshot #covidnurse

column31: Vitamin D is critical for many functions in the body, including bone growth, reducing inflammation, immune health, reducing the likelihood of depression (especially related to seasonal affective disorder), and decreasing the risk of colorectal and breast cancer.⁣ ⁣ Unfortunately, research has found that about ¼ of the US population is deficient in Vitamin D, with higher rates in countries that are further north, like Canada and Europe.⁣ Is your Diet Providing Enough Vitamin D? If you suffer any of the following problems, you might consider eating more vitamin D rich food sources, more sunlight and/or supplementation. -Tooth Decay -Bleeding gums and gum disease -Irritable bowel disease or other digestive conditions -Auto-immune conditions -Type-II diabetes -Snoring, teeth grinding or sleep apnea -Arthritis, sore joints, back, and neck pain -Brain-fog, dementia, Alzheimer’s disease - VIRUS/IMMUNE concerns Why are vitamin D rich diets so rare today? It wasn’t until recently, that we began to understand that vitamin D is synthesized by exposure to the sun. Strong bones and teeth need vitamin D. The osteo-immune system is hungry for vitamin D to control hormonal signaling for your bones and immune system. Vitamin D deficiency is thought to increase the risk of tooth decay and gum disease. Low-fat diets have stripped vitamin D from the diet. The trend in the last 50 years to eat low-fat foods Vitamin D is linked to many chronic diseases including digestive, auto-immune, and mental conditions. 3 WAYS TO GET VITAMIN D ⬇ ⁣ 1. SUNLIGHT⁣ ☀️ The body can make its own Vitamin D when the skin is exposed to sunlight. However, if you’re living above a latitude of 37 degrees north, your skin makes little Vitamin D from the sun except during the summer months.⁣ ⁣ 10-15 minutes of sun on the face and arms, 2-3 times of week will meet most people’s requirements. However, this also varies based on age, skin color, sunscreen use, pollution, and cloud cover.⁣ ⁣ Therefore, it’s important to get Vitamin D from other sources as well.⁣ ⁣ 2. FOOD SOURCES⁣ 🐠 • Oily fish (salmon, sardines, herring)⁣ • Red meat⁣ • Liver⁣ • Egg yolks⁣ • Ghee • Mushrooms (the only good plant source of vitamin D)⁣ ⁣ 3. SUPPLEMENTATION⁣ 💊 Vitamin D deficiency is still an issue, so supplementation is often necessary. Generally, a supplement of 2000-5000IU is a good option during the fall and winter months (at higher latitudes), or year-round if you have darker skin. However, this recommendation can differ between individuals, that’s why it is always recommended to get tested before, so you should speak to a doctor about your specific situation.⁣ If you test (+) positive: ~4000-10,000IU. . . . column31: When looking for the best oils for skin, knowing what skin type you have is only half the battle. It’s also really important to understand an oil’s comedogenic rating – that is, how likely it will clog pores. This time of year, the focus turns inward. Partially into our homes to decorate and warm ourselves, and partially how to keep our inner bodies healthy. The colder months typically mean worse autoimmune symptoms, more illness, and dry or problem skin. Lotions line store shelves promising to heal and moisturize skin, but they rarely work and usually contain a host of chemicals. No, thanks. Oils may be ideal for dry skin, oily skin, acne prone skin, what’s called combination skin, or just regular, old “normal” skin. Know what skin type you have so you know what type of oil to match that. It’s really important to understand an oil’s comedogenic rating – that is, how likely it will clog pores. While there are many oils that can be nourishing, they aren’t much help if they clog your pores and cause blackheads and breakouts. We use these beneficial oils in our skin care products!

column36:
News, California: National Informed Consent Exemption (NICE) proposed.  

On February 22, 2021 (George Washington’s Birthday), constitutional litigators Greg Glaser and Ray Flores will appear in Federal Court (Eastern District of California, Department 5) to request a National Informed Consent Exemption (NICE).  According to Glaser’s court documents, “America has been segregated by vaccination status, such as public schools for the vaccinated, but homeschools for the unvaccinated; employment opportunity for the vaccinated, but self-employment for the unvaccinated. Separate is not equal.  As such, the purpose of this Motion for Preliminary Injunction is to protect Petitioners from further discrimination and threats, and to request the Court protect individuals as potential candidates for scientific control group surveys and studies. This end can be achieved by the Court simply issuing a preservation of evidence order that upholds the right and ethic of informed consent/refusal, by prohibiting discrimination on the basis of vaccination status.”

Glaser says that NICE would exempt all Americans from mandatory vaccination.

To show public support for the NICE order, Glaser is asking fellow Americans to sign the White House petition for NICE: 
https://petitions.whitehouse.gov/petition/approve-national-informed-consent-exemption-vaccination

column31: Scientists and doctors have been aware that vaccines can cause seizures, paralysis, and brain inflammation and or deterioration for decades: “Encephalopathies following prophylactic use of pertussis vaccine.” 1948 “Neurological Complication After Combined Diphtheria and Pertussis Immunization”, 1950 is a case report of a one-year-old girl who suffered from convulsions and paralysis of one side of the body the morning after an injection of alum-precipitated pertussis vaccine and diphtheria A.P.T. “CONVULSIONS AND HEMIPLEGIA IN PERTUSSIS PROPHYLAXIS“, 1950 details the case reports of a 7-month-old girl and a 3-year-old girl who experienced convulsions immediately after injection of triple antigen (vintage name for DPT). “[Subcortical dementia with pseudofocal motor disorders: mental deficiency in a 9-year old girl after whooping cough vaccination].” 1953 “Encephalopathy Following Diphtheria-pertussis Inoculation”, 1953 “Neurological Complications of Pertussis Immunization”, Berg. 1958 “Further Experience of Reactions, Especially of a Cerebral Nature, in Conjunction with Triple Vaccination: A Study Based on Vaccinations in Sweden 1959-65”, 1967 “Immunisation and brain damage.” 1977 Barlow et al. (2001) found: “Receipt of DTP vaccine was associated with an increased risk of febrile seizures only on the day of vaccination (adjusted relative risk, 5.70; 95 percent confidence interval, 1.98 to 16.42).” “Receipt of MMR vaccine was associated with an increased risk of febrile seizures 8 to 14 days after vaccination (relative risk, 2.83; 95 percent confidence interval, 1.44 to 5.55).” Miller et al. (2007) found: “An elevated relative incidence of convulsion was found in the 6- to 11-day period after receipt of Priorix (relative incidence = 6.26, 95% confidence interval: 3.85, 10.18)-consistent with the known effects of the measles component of MMR vaccine” Full post: https://circleofmamas.com/health-news/vaccines-and-seizures/ #seizure #seizures #epilepsy #epilepsyawareness #epilepsywarrior #seizureawareness #seizuressuck #epileptic #seizuredisorder #infantilespasms

column31: Key Safety Concerns. The four key safety concerns specified in the petition11 to the European Medicine Agency are: 1.The potential for formation of non-neutralizing antibodies that can trigger an exaggerated immune reaction (referred to as paradoxical immune enhancement or antibody-dependent immune amplification) when the individual is exposed to the real "wild" virus post-vaccination. Antibody-dependent amplification has been repeatedly demonstrated in coronavirus vaccine trials on animals.12 While the animals initially tolerated the vaccine well and had robust immune responses, they later became severely ill or died when infected with the wild virus. Put plainly, the vaccine increased their susceptibility to the virus and made them more likely to die from the infection. 2.Pfizer's mRNA vaccine contains polyethylene glycol (PEG), and studies have shown 70% of people develop antibodies against this substance. This suggests PEG may trigger fatal allergic reactions in many who receive the vaccine. Indeed, within days of the vaccine's release, reports started coming in of people having life-threatening anaphylactic reactions,13 leading to warnings that people with known allergies should not take the Pfizer vaccine.14 Since then, anaphylactic reactions have been reported by recipients of the Moderna mRNA vaccine as well.15 3.The mRNA vaccine triggers your body to produce antibodies against the SARS-CoV-2 spike protein, and spike proteins in turn contain syncytin-homologous proteins that are essential for the formation of placenta. If a woman's immune system starts reacting against syncytin-1, then there is the possibility she could become infertile. This is an issue that none of the vaccine studies is looking at specifically. Mass vaccinating women of childbearing age against COVID-19 could potentially have the devastating consequence of causing mass infertility if the vaccine triggers an immune reaction against syncytin-1. The petition states that this possibility must be "absolutely ruled out" before mass vaccination takes place. 4.The studies are far too brief in duration to allow a realistic estimation of side effects. Depending on what those effects end up being, millions of people may be exposed to unacceptable risk in return for a very minor benefit. Link in comments.

column36:
Before I start this post I am in no way feeding into conspiracies, lies etc this is from true experience and i am currently having to write this with one hand. Today I went in for my pfizer covid 19 vaccination because i work in a care home and thought it would be in best interest of my residents to have it i was offered a choice! before i had the jab i was asked if i had any allergies which i stated a mild egg allergy so after my jab i was told to stay for a 30 minute observation to see if the vaccine caused a anaphylactic reaction. I was fine apart from a mild headache i put that down to not eating properly when i got home i decided to go for a nap which lasted an hour little did i know everything was going to get worse. When i woke up i could barely feel my right side (i was vaccinated in my right arm) and could barely string a sentence together i had slurred speech and little energy. as time went on i lost complete sensation in my right arm and leg and my headache became an excruciating pain in my neck aswell, my mum suspected something was wrong and called 111 for some advice as we weren’t sure if these are normal side effects. When speaking to 111 they sent an ambulance which came in 10 minutes, i was assessed and sent to the royal hospital i was then sent for a CT scan and admitted as a potential stroke bearing in mind i am 19 years old. the CT scan was clear but there was no explanation for the loss of feeling in my body I am now on a stroke ward despite no sign of a stroke to monitor if my feeling comes back and to see if i can walk again.
So please unless you need this vaccination refrain from getting it because we all know what is the reason i am in this state right now but they refuse to say it!
UPDATE. i put this post for awareness not to be trolled and called a liar when i am currently unable to even go to the toilet without full assistance today i managed to take a step using the whole strength in my body. i would never lie about something so serious.
I’d like to add another update and progress video as no i don’t think i have to prove myself but just show the seriousness of my situation. This video was during my therapy session on trying to get my arm moving again i used all the strength i have to try and move a fork to my mouth. I have not once said anti vaccine etc i decided to take it i simply just shared what has happened to me.

A 45-year-old nurse in California tested positive for COVID-19 more than a week after receiving Pfizer Inc's coronavirus vaccine, an ABC News affiliate reported on Tuesday.
.
Matthew W, a nurse at two different local hospitals, said in a Facebook post on December 18 that he had received the Pfizer vaccine, telling the ABC News affiliate that his arm was sore for a day but that he had suffered no other side-effects. Six days later on Christmas Eve, he became sick after working a shift in the COVID-19 unit, the report added. He got the chills and later came down with muscle aches and fatigue.

column36:
Edit to add: Dawson was officially diagnosed with Autism Spectrum Disorder on Aug. 20th. And yes, we know about TRS and nemechek protocol. 

This is the hardest thing I’ve ever written... I may forget everything I want to say, and I may just ramble, but I’m looking for some light at the end of the tunnel. This is our story...

I have 3 sons, Nolan who will be 12 this winter and is from a previous relationship, Dawson who is 17 months and my second son but my husband’s first son, and Leonidas that is 5 1/2 months old, also with my husband. 

Dawson came after multiple losses. He was so loved before even being born, so anticipated, and such a blessing after so much heartache.  He was so silly, engaging, beautiful, full of life, speaking, and was hitting all other milestones like a champ prior to his 12 month vaccines.  Then came the vaccines and along came a change that I never in my life thought I’d have to experience. Like the flip of a switch, the boy we grew to know and love was gone. The light in our sons eyes went out, almost leaving an emptiness in his beautiful blue eyes that is heartbreaking everytime I think about it.  He stopped speaking, started OBSESSING over one particular show, started to become obsessed with things that had to do with hand sensory (dragging hands on carpet, grass, brushes, etc... over and over and over...) stopped wanting to make eye contact, no longer wanted to cuddle, stopped non-verbal communications like pointing and waving, stopped actually playing with toys and rather messes with certain objects in a way that comes off as OCD rituals, in my opinion, prefers to climb, spin, or run back and forth over and over, NEVER EVER EVER answers to his name, started to fall a lot, and does what we have found through research is called, “verbal and hand stimming”, the list goes on and on... (after we noticed this he did get ear tubes placed, we see a slight difference, but nothing super exciting...)

We made an appointment with the pediatrician, expressed our concerns, and were thankfully “heard” by her. She has referred us for autism testing, we quickly filled out and returned the paperwork from the behavioral specialist who will do an in person eval, and are also awaiting the state programs for in home assessment for things like speech therapy, etc... we 100% are prepared for a diagnosis of ASD. He just turned 17 months, but we could tell something happened and that he was “different” than before at 12 months. Has anyone had success with intense therapy? We know everyone’s outcome can vary, but need to hear stories of hope in our dark times. 

If you made it this far, thank you in advance! I’m including pics of my little guy, 1 before the vaccines, and 1 after.

column31: If you’ve recently had a blood test, you might assume it would show a magnesium deficiency. But only 1 percent of magnesium in your body is distributed in your blood, making a simple sample of magnesium from a serum magnesium blood test not very useful. Most magnesium is stored in your bones and organs, where it is used for many biological functions. Yet, it’s quite possible to be deficient and not know it, which is why magnesium deficiency has been dubbed the “invisible deficiency."

column31: Pfizer is one of the largest pharmaceutical companies in the world. The Pfizer COVID v@xxyne was approved for emergency use by the FDA on Dec. 11th 2020. But who is Pfizer? How much do we really know about them? Turns out they have a pretty long rap sheet! 1980s - Pfizer’s widely prescribed arthritis drug Feldene created a high risk of gastrointestinal bleeding among the elderly, but the federal government, despite reports of scores of fatalities, declined to put restrictions on the medication. 1986 - Pfizer’s Shiley division knowingly produced and sold defective heart valves that killed at the least 125 people. By 1991 these valves has been implanted into tens of thousands of people. The FDA task force charged that Shiley had withheld information about safety problems from regulators in order to get initial approval for its valves and that the company continued to keep the FDA in the dark. Faced with this growing scandal. Pfizer announced that it would spend up to $205 million to settle the tens of thousands of valve lawsuits that had been filed against it. 1991 - Pfizer paid a total of $70,000 to 10 states to settle charges relating to misleading advertising for its Plax mouth rinse. 1999 - Pfizer pleaded guilty to criminal antitrust charges that its former Food Science Group unit took part in two international price-fixing conspiracies—one involving the food preservative sodium erythorbate and the other the flavor enhancer maltol. Pfizer agreed to pay fines totaling $20 million. 2003 - Pfizer paid $6 million to settle with 19 states that had accused the company of using misleading ads to promote its Zithromax medication for children’s ear infections. 2004 - Pfizer’s Warner-Lambert subsidiary agreed to pay $430 million to resolve criminal and civil charges that it paid physicians to prescribe its epilepsy drug Neurontin to patients with ailments for which the medication was not approved. 2004 - In the wake of revelations about dangerous side effects of Merck’s painkiller Vioxx, Pfizer agreed to suspend television advertising for a related medication called Celebrex. The following year, Pfizer admitted that a 1999 clinical trial found that elderly patients taking Celebrex had a greatly elevated risk of heart problems. 2005 - Pfizer withdrew another painkiller, Bextra, from the market after the FDA mandated a “black box” warning about the cardiovascular and gastrointestinal risks of the medication. In 2008 Pfizer announced that it was setting aside $894 million to settle the lawsuits that had been filed in connection with Bextra and Celebrex. 2009 - Pfizer agreed to pay $2.3 billion to resolve criminal and civil charges relating to the improper marketing of Bextra and three other medications. 2009 - The company had to pay a record $2.3 billion to settle federal charges that one of its subsidiaries had illegally marketed a painkiller called Bextra. 2010 - A federal jury awarded $1.37 million to a former Pfizer scientist who claimed she was sickened by a genetically engineered virus at a company lab and was then fired for raising safety concerns. 2011 - Pfizer agreed to pay $14.5 million to resolve federal charges that it illegally marketed its bladder drug Detrol. This isn't even the entire list and as you can see, this is a notoriously corrupt company! And they really expect us to trust them with this rushed v@xxyne?

column31: Public post from Jennifer Denton: “The last 8 days have been incredibly challenging. I had little interest in sharing the details of our lives publicly but through our experience is has become clear that information to help those suffering from the CV va((ine is minimal. Public groups to share experiences with the vaccine have been actively deleting posts describing my husband’s experience as it doesn’t follow the message they want you to hear. “Before jumping in, I’d like clarify that my husband is a frontline worker in healthcare and has been serving his community in various ways for 10+ years. I’d also like to say thank you to every single individual who has reached out to my husband and me to offer comfort and support. We appreciate you. “On December 26th my husband received the Mo_d_erna CV va((ine. Shortly after, he developed a slight fever and general exhaustion. The following day came with incredible challenges that resulted in my husband being bedridden. Whole body exhaustion, incredibly high fevers, chills, headaches, nausea. He could barely pick his arm up... “Enter Monday, 12/28. On 1,000 mgs of Tylenol and 800 mgs of Motrin (ibuprofen), he was throwing temperatures higher than 104. I brought him to a local emergency room where he was told to treat his symptoms like virus until proven otherwise... they gave him IV fluids and sent him on his way... “While waiting for his ultimately negative results (he does not have the virus) I called numerous urgent care centers who refused to see him, on-call doctors for ECHN who refused to provide medical advice over the phone to an ECHN patient (isn’t that their job?! Said doctor also informed me 104 fevers were ‘not dangerous’ and the ice packs and cold cloths we were placing on his body were ‘only going to make me feel better and won’t do anything for him.’) We were left alone with minimal guidance from professionals in the field my husband has been working in for over a decade... “You may be thinking, ‘Why didn’t you call the va((ine hotline?’ We did. It was our first call. They picked up and said to report symptoms online for tracking purposes and then hung up. There was no guidance for treatment, no recommendations for who to seek help from...nothing more than, ‘hope you feel better.’ “Fast forward a bit. Symptoms continued to worsen and I ultimately brought him to a privately held highly regarded emergency room in Hartford, CT for further care. Without sharing specifics, I’ll share that my husband was and continues to be so incredibly ill, the hospital has been testing every potential cause for his symptoms which has included 20+ tests and counting: - Countless X-rays, - Multiple Ultrasounds, - Spinal taps for meningitis, and - Regular ongoing blood work for blood bacteria, to name a few. “Doctors and nurses from Infectious Disease have been consulting with each other to try and best identify potential trial treatments to see what works and what doesn’t. For now, he’s been given anti-bacterial medication in an attempt to relieve his symptoms. “My husband after four days still remains in the hands of caring, interested, and well researched professionals who are the ONLY professionals who have taken a general interest in helping, researching, and trying. “At the end of the day, I am beyond thankful for this privately held highly regarded Hartford-based hospital, but am very concerned about how little is being shared in regards to CV va((ine symptoms and their severity. “Two days ago I saw a big push to get the va((ine on the news with a tempting promise of a ‘normal Fall’ if we all get va((inated... please take our experiences into consideration as you decide what is best for you and your family. “And if you’ve taken some time out of your day to read through this, please SHARE. There is little information available for those suffering. And if for any reason you become increasingly ill, please seek help from the best hospital you can as soon as you can. “If you have any questions regarding my husband, his experience or mine, please reach out. I want you to be armed with information about ALL side effects from the vaccine so you can make the best decisions for you and your families. “With every wish that you and yours stay safe and well, Jen.” P.S. Vaccination simulates infection in the body, whilst trying to avoid full-blown infection. Vaccines that are injected intramuscularly: DTaP, HIB, Hep B, Hep A, HPV, Influenza, Men, PCV, Polio. Vaccines that are injected subcutaneously: MMR, PPSV, Polio, Zoster, MMRV, Varicella. Vaccines that are oral: Rotavirus. Why should we worry about injection? In 1913, Charles Richet received the Nobel Prize for his discovery that giving a parenteral injection of a colloid or protein substance or a toxin caused ‘anaphylaxis’. The discovery of the phenomenon of anaphylaxis showed that by immunization not only protection but also harmful events could be induced. (Ring) Prior to this, anaphylaxis was observed from snake bites and bee or wasp stings–we did not have any anaphylactic food allergies before the routine use of injections in infant medical care. We didn’t have a surge in autoimmune diseases like celiac disease, rheumatoid arthritis, type-1 diabetes, or multiple sclerosis before routine use of injections in infant medical care. column31: When experiencing health challenges, many times we’re so desperate to receive a diagnosis so that we can FINALLY validate and label our symptoms. For many, I think it means that we are not just “making stuff up” in our head, but that there was actually a NAME to what we are going through. However, I can assure you that the diagnostic “label” ultimately provides a huge disservice to you. True healing comes from getting to the root cause of these symptoms. And for everyone, even with the same "diagnosis" it's different and unique. What toxins🦠 need to be removed (from the body and the environment)? What emotional injuries are affecting our tissues and glands? What pathogens🧫 or coinfections are lingering? What drainage pathways are stagnant, keeping the body from being able to adequately remove these pathogens and toxins? Instead of diagnosing someone with hypothyroidism and giving them levothyroxine💊, why aren’t we also assessing their exposure to pesticides (I have seen this with farmers, lawn care workers and florists), medorrhinum miasm (hyperfunction) or Psora miasm (hypofunction), heavy metals, especially lead and mercury, fluoride, chlorine, or bromine which can directly affect thyroid receptors? Instead of diagnosing someone with irritable bowel syndrome, why aren’t we diving into assessing for parasites🐛 such as cryptosporidium, entamoeba and toxoplasmosis or other pathogens and toxins such as shigella and mycobacterium that cause the bowels to be irritable in the first place? How about trapped emotional injury such as fear of not being good enough, shame and abuse? Until we get to the root cause, all we’re doing is band-aiding symptoms and driving underpinnings in deeper. It's important to address the root cause and practice the idea of first principles. You start with any idea or assumption, and then you ask why, and then you ask why again, and again. And when you get to the point where there's no more whys you can answer, you've likely arrived at the potential first principle. Basically dig deeper and deeper until you are left with only foundational truths of an idea or situation root cause principle. René Descartes was a French philosopher and a scientist, and he talked about this approach, and a method that's now called Cartesian doubt, in which he would systematically doubt everything he could possibly doubt until he was left with what he saw as purely indisputable truths. So basically boil things down until they can't be boiled down anymore. Or in layman's terms, this is basically the practice of questioning everything you think you know, about any problems, scenario, belief, and then creating new knowledge and solutions from scratch, operating only on those things, those truths, and not scenarios, systems, or assumptions that are just built on those = root cause truth. But being in this field for decades, many want to take a pill and not address the core underpinnings, I'm seeing it now even in the events of the world. I pray this post serves as a reminder to practice first principles for you to look further than just a symptom or diagnosis, to continue asking WHY until you get to YOUR root causes. column31: When I’m confused by the present, I look to the past. 🙂 The above quote is from a Christian from the 17th century. The writer was reminding the church to avoid division and strife by staying focused on what matters: faith in Jesus. Non-essentials included dogma that didn’t appear in the Bible. And the call to charity was really a call to love one another above all else. It seems so fitting for these times: a call to unity, liberty, & love. To my mind, the essentials today include 🙏🏼 faith 🤗 family 🥰 our common humanity Non-essentials include ❌ political party affiliations ❌ masks v. no masks ❌ pro-vaccine or anti-vax Overall, love for each other, whatever is going on & wherever we stand, is critical. column31: Being a natural/holistic mama is not about the choices you make (entirely). It's mostly about the mindset with which you make choices. Holistic/natural means believing that the body CAN be whole and healthy, that it's meant to be, but that our world is less-than-optimal and we have to remove toxic influences and provide natural foods, herbs, and mindfulness in order to restore health. It means supporting the body's needs so that it can do its job. Choosing anything that 'corrects' a body's "natural deficiency" is to believe that the body *cannot* be healthy without modern intervention, and goes against the very core belief of holistic health. Therefore...you cannot support v@xxynes, circumcision, vitamin K shot, prophylactic antibiotics, and other practices and be truly holistic, because these go against the holistic mindset. All try to "fix" the body before there is ever a problem. All say the body is not good enough or strong enough in its natural state. Breastfeeding a baby does not make someone holistic. Eating unprocessed food does not make someone holistic. We say this not to judge where a person is on their path, but to define what "holistic" really means. There are people who do not aspire to be holistic who will still make some healthy choices, and that's great. Right now, being "natural" is trendy, for better or worse (and sometimes it's both). "Mainstream natural," which is not at all holistic, is trying to drown out the voices of those who are actually holistic. To say they don't matter or are too extreme or crazy. It gets to be confusing for moms who want to do better and aren't sure what to do or how to think. Holistic is a mindset. A way of evaluating choices and coming to conclusions. Not a set of exact decisions. (And yes, you CAN be holistic even if you don't do everything 'perfectly,' because none of us do. It goes back to mindset, and admitting when you do something that's not optimal and not feeling guilty about that.) Are you a mainstream 'natural' mama or a 'holistic' mama? There is room for both...but they are different. Personally, I'm a holistic mama. 🙂

column31: Obsetrician Dr. Gregory Michael was a healthy 56-year-old obstetrician when he got the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine on December 18th, said his wife Heidi Neckelman, in a Facebook post shared over 10,000 times. He was active and had no pre-existing conditions, but after the shot, things took a turn for the worse. Dr. Michael developed Idiopathic Thrombocytopenia Purpura (ITP), which is an autoimmune illness that causes the body to destroy its own platelets, the tiny fragments that help blood to clot. Autoimmune means that something in the vaccine may be provoking the body to create antibodies to its own platelets, could be because of molecular mimicry, or cross reactivity between proteins. ITP has been documented to occur after the MMR vaccine, as well as influenza vaccines, DTP vaccine and hepatitis A vaccines. Three days after getting the experimental vaccine, Dr. Michael noticed petechiae – spots of red that indicate bleeding beneath the skin – on his feet and hands. When he checked himself into Mount Sinai Medical Center in Miami Beach, the hospital where he works and had the groundbreaking vaccine, medics discovered he was suffering from an acute lack of platelets. ‘All the blood results came back normal except for the platelets which came back as zero,’ Heidi said. https://circleofmamas.com/health-news/florida-doctor-dies-after-getting-covid-vaccine/

column31: Keratosis pilaris or “chicken skin,” is a very common skin condition that causes patches of rough-feeling bumps to appear on the skin. These tiny bumps or pimples are actually dead skin cells plugging hair follicles. Keratosis pilaris is normally found on the arms, thighs, cheeks, or buttocks. This condition is known to worsen in the winter months when the skin tends to dry out, and may also worsen during pregnancy.

column31: Is it Just The Baby Blues? Many new mothers have the “baby blues” after childbirth. This is characterized as crying, mood swings, anxiety and difficulty sleeping according to the Mayo Clinic. Symptoms typically begin within a few short days after delivery, and can last around two weeks. The key here is that these feelings go away fairly quickly. Or is it Postpartum Depression? Sometimes symptoms may start off more subtly and be mistaken for the baby blues. But if the funk you are in becomes more intense and lasts longer, you may have postpartum depression. If you are struggling with postpartum depression know that you are not alone. It is more common than people realize. There are several ways to treat this naturally. But if you believe your depression is severe, please get help immediately. There is no shame in seeking help! Want information on naturally treating postpartum depression? Let us know and we'd be happy to help!
column34: Do you suffer from Postpartum Depression? Symptoms include: .Severe mood swings •Excessive crying Difficulty bonding with your baby •Withdrawing from family and friends Change in eating habits Difficulty sleeping Overwhelming fatigue .Intense irritability and anger Feelings of worthlessness or guilt Difficulty concentrating Severe anxiety and panic attacks Postpartum depression can happen to any mother. But just like other mental illnesses, postpartum depression still has stigma around it, and does not get near the discussion it warrants. Earthley weliness

column31: "This young man approached me and asked me to buy him a gallon of milk. My first thought was to say no but as I was paying for my gas I grabbed the milk. Outside was his girlfriend holding a box of cereal. He thanked me and I started to walk to my car. Something in me made me turn around. I told them I was about to get a car wash but if he wanted to wash it for me I’d pay him $20. We went to the nearest car wash and he had tears in his eyes after I paid him! He told me that more than anything he appreciated me giving him the opportunity to be a man again in the eyes of his girlfriend and work for the money. The whole time his girlfriend helped him. It’s like she was proud of him. You could tell the love was so real. Real beyond material things and what he could do for her. She told him he did a great job and he couldn’t stop smiling. I had a long talk with him and her and he had a backpack full of paperwork from all of the places he’s been going to get help for them. I drove them to my apartment complex and gave him clothes for interviews and a few outfits and fitted caps. I don’t have much but life is about sharing what you do have. Be a blessing to someone today because you could be in that situation before you know it! I gave them my number and I plan to take them to any interviews or appointments they have. It’s a great day to be alive no matter what your situation is. Someone has it worse than you! Share this message and inspire others to do good.” Credit: Ariane Nelson See Less
